# Fix N+1 Query Inefficiencies in Django Ninja API

The application uses Django Ninja with schema-driven serialization. When a schema references nested relations (e.g., `BoardSchema.lists`, `TaskCardSchema.checklists`), Django Ninja resolves them by accessing the related manager — which fires a **separate SQL query per parent object** unless the queryset is pre-fetched.

Only [kanban/api.py](file:///c:/Users/Eridu/OneDrive/Desktop/Mthds/backend/kanban/api.py) is wired into the URL config; [board/api.py](file:///c:/Users/Eridu/OneDrive/Desktop/Mthds/backend/board/api.py) is a vestigial module but will be fixed for completeness.

